summary: An Ordinance authorizing a temporary re-routing of cars on the Fremont-Ballard, 6th Avenue N. W., and Phinney Avenue lines, and providing for the operation of cars by one man on each car on that portion of the route described in Ordinance No. 5874 of the City of Seattle, which extended from Stone Avenue and Westlake to the south side of the Fremont Bridge Florentia Street.
